com.mobius.vdrapi.command
Class CommandKeyType

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--com.mobius.vdrapi.command.CommandKeyType
public final class CommandKeyType
extends Object

This class provides a lst of the available command keys. Command keys specify parameters for a command object. For example, in the following command, DOCUMENTSERVER is a command key. 

LOCATENODE DOCUMENTSERVER 'Richs Server'

numberOfValues

public int numberOfValues(String keyValue)
                   throws ValueInvalidException
Returns the number of values this command key can have. This number is dependent upon the key value.

Command keys can have zero or more associated values. For example, the PAGES command key can be one of the following:

  • ALL
  • ALLINSECTION
  • FROM X Y

Returns:
the number of values expected for this key.
Throws:
ValueInvalidException - thrown if the key value is used, but is not a valid value.
